engineDB::testConnection()

Description
    public bool engineDB::testConnection([bool $reconnect = FALSE])
    Checks whether or not the connection to the server is working.

Parameters
    reconnect
	Boolean value.  If the value is set to TRUE then the object will attempt to connect to the server.

Return Values
    Returns FALSE if the connection to the server is not working.  Returns TRUE otherwise.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	function select_db($db) {
	    $this->testConnection(TRUE);
	    
	    if(!isset($db)) {
		return(FALSE)
	    }
	...

See Also
    engineDB::test()
